Kabiru Dogo, the coach of Wikki Tourists of Bauchi, has continue to lament his side’s 3-0 loss to Abia War­riors in Okigwe in one of the match day ten of the season, saying his wards must get it right on Sun­day against Rangers Inter­national. Recall that Dogo was left dejected at the Okigwe Township Stadium where Abia Warriors turned his Wikki side to real Tourists on the pitch The Matchday 10 fixture of the Nigeria Professional Football League (NPFL) had Abia Warriors written all over it, as they delivered a command performance that condemned Wikki Tourist to 3-0 annihilation in a very entertaining game. 3SC Promise To Build On Heartland Massacre This Weekend Ilechukwu Promises To Ride On Plateau’s Win At Rangers Dogo did not hide his disappointment with the overall performance of his wards and chided them for not being clinical despite creating opportunities. Dogo did not hide his disappointment with the overall performance of his wards and chided them for not being clinical despite creating chances. While regretting the poor result, Dogo said: “That was not a good game for us be­cause we prepared for it; at worst we would have picked a draw not a loss”, Dogo lamented and threw in the blame. “My players simply could not raise their game that day, missing begging chanc­es and they were just not clinical in front of goal even after creating the chances. “We will try and erase this loss in our next game because we didn’t anticipate this loss and this poor goal margin also,” he said.